         <abstract>
            <p>The asymptotic behavior of the integral $$I(\lambda) = \int^{\pi/2}_0 J^2_0(\lambda \sin x) dx$$ is investigated, where $J_0(x)$ is the zeroth-order Bessel function of the first kind and $\lambda$ is a large positive parameter. A practical analytical expression of the integral at large $\lambda$ is obtained and the leading term is $(\ln \lambda)/(\lambda\pi)$.</p>
          </abstract>
